Bishop Daniel A. Payne was
an AME Church leader and an
active educator, during the Civil
War.

In March 1868, he bought Will
berforce University for $4,000
from the Methodist Episcopal
Church Gan all white group.

WASHINGTON Secretary of
Labor w. Willard Wirtz In his
report to Congress on the first
full year Of operations under
the Manpower Development and
Training Act. noted that the eff
fects of lack of schooling are so
drastic in the case of some
youths. that not only are they un-
able to find any employment for
which they are qualified. he added
they are virtually incapable of
being trained for a vocation and
job.


The Secretary called attention
to the fact that nearly one-fourth
of the manpower program train
ees at the present time are nom
white - about the same proper
tion as this group represented
among all unemployed persons
in 1868. More than 40 percent
of all trainees we're women.


The typical trainee in 1868
was a young adult with family
responsibilities. Two-thirds Of
the male trainees were heads of
households. Six out of ten were
primary wage earners. Most Of
the trainees were high school
graduates.

LEOPOLDVILLE. The Congo
Three Italian priests have fled
their mission in Kivu Province
after an attack by knife WELD
ing terrorists.


Sources said the priests had
arrived at Belgian-run sugar
refinery near Uvira. They ap-
parently walked about 20 miles
through rugged, mountainous
Country from their mission at
Mulenge.
